<figureCitation id="13542A0F103E7310FBBBFE67DBD6ACBF" box="[1090,1219,413,437]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Figs" captionStart-2="Figs" captionStartId-0="14.[836,871,2060,2082]" captionStartId-1="16.[836,880,1975,1997]" captionStartId-2="17.[812,857,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox-0="[835,1473,862,2037]" captionTargetBox-1="[838,1478,821,1938]" captionTargetBox-2="[820,1447,612,1899]" captionTargetId-0="figure-215@14.[835,1476,859,2040]" captionTargetId-1="figure-8@16.[818,1490,804,1958]" captionTargetId-2="figure-15@17.[796,1475,530,1911]" captionTargetPageId-0="14" captionTargetPageId-1="16" captionTargetPageId-2="17" captionText-0="Fig. 30. Laccotrephes simulatus Montandon, male, specimen from Malaysia, Johor." captionText-1="Figs. 31–34. Laccotrephes species, prosterna, left lateral views (FC = fore coxa, PS = prosternum, PP = propleuron). 31, L. pfeiferiae. 32, L. archipelagi, specimen from Malaysia, Johor. 33, L. simulatus, specimen from Malaysia, Johor. 34, L. longicaudatus, specimen from Malaysia, Johor." captionText-2="Figs. 35–38. Laccotrephes species, male parameres, left lateral views (all to same scale). 35, L. longicaudatus, specimen from Malaysia, Johor. 36, L. simulatus, specimen from Malaysia, Johor. 37, L. archipelagi, specimen from Malaysia, Johor (paramere apex only). 38, L. pfeiferiae, specimen from Laos, Vientiane Prov. (paramere apex only)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351534" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351536" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351538" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5351534/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5351536/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5351538/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">Figs. 30–38</figureCitation>
